x, colonialism, and belonging. Other chapters discuss topics like prostitution, same-sex intimacy, sexual violence, interracial romance, and marriage with an impressive level of detail and complexity. Written in vivid and accessible prose, West of Sex offers readers a new vision of sex and race in American history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMarginality, SocialxHistoryx20th centuryxSouthwest, New. 0aMarginality, SocialzSouthwest, NewxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexicansxSexual behaviorxHistoryx20th centuryxSouthwest, New. 0aMexicansxSexual behaviorzSouthwest, NewxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexicansxSocial conditionsxHistoryx20th centuryxSouthwest, New. 0aMexicanszSouthwest, NewxSocial conditionsxHistoryy20th century. 0aSex crimesxHistoryx20th centuryxSouthwest, New. 0aSex crimeszSouthwest, NewxHistoryy20th century. 0aSexxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aSexxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aTrials (Sex crimes)xCasesxSouthwest, New. 0aTrials (Sex crimes)zSouthwest, NewvCases. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226532738423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226532738.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles